  "title": "Supply Chain Management, Senior Executive (Regional Trade Compliance)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Lead trade compliance activities (STC), ensuring full adherence to import/export regulations and Free Trade Agreement (FTA) requirements across the Southeast Asia region.</li>\n  <li>Manage and analyze supply chain data to produce insightful, up-to-date reports that support operational improvements.</li>\n  <li>Design and maintain visual dashboards for effective management reporting and performance tracking.</li>\n  <li>Drive supply chain initiatives at ESP to ensure cost-efficiency, quality, and full regulatory compliance.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all departmental regulations, processes, and workflows are regularly reviewed and updated in line with policy and regulatory changes.</li>\n  <li>Conduct training and internal audits to reinforce compliance and operational standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Key Contributions</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain full compliance with trade regulations and chemical controls, achieving zero compliance incidents.</li>\n  <li>Develop and implement customized BI dashboards and reports to improve supply chain data visibility and strategic decision-making.</li>\n  <li>Identify areas for improvement through data-driven analysis and lead initiatives to enhance supply chain efficiency.</li>\n  <li>Ensure timely follow-through and successful completion of assigned projects.</li>\n  <li>Oversee the continuous alignment of SCM processes and workflows with current business and regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Deliver SEC-defined compliance training programs and facilitate STC/BCP audits in collaboration with regional ESC teams.</li>\n  <li>Implement tailored internal control procedures to support corporate governance and risk management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No. 20C0270</p>",
